Body: Sharing economy – as the basis for the economy of the future  We are living in the era of global change and the fact that yesterday something was still on the verge of science fiction is already becoming a reality today. And this applies not only to new products in the field of science and technology, it is primarily reflected in the worldview and lifestyle of modern society. Business and economics are transforming from private to global and not limited in space, especially in the areas of information. And one of the catalysts of this process is the sharing-economy. The main idea and goal are the transformation of production and consumption – the participants share things, objects, without taking them into ownership.  According to forecasts, by 2025, the world economy will increase by almost 20 times and reach $ 335 billion. Danish deputy Ida Auken has made even more global forecasts, suggesting that by 2030 people will abandon property as such. In the column for Weforum, she suggested exactly how it will be and what benefits it will bring to the society. Ida Auken said that first of all means of communication will become free of charge, then energy, transport and other goods. Due to the abandonment of car ownership, traffic jams will disappear and air pollution will be reduced. The use of leased goods will force manufacturers to extend their lifespan. The amount of necessary expenses will decrease, which means the need for earnings, it will increase the amount of free time for creativity and self-development.  Syntera believes that the sharing economy is the future. One of our current projects which is being developed is the Syntera Marketplace blockchain platform. The main directions are renting or leasing any resource, joint ownership, co-renting, organizing joint purchases of goods or services, and much more.  Read more https://syntera.io/articles/130

Body: Perspectives and advantages of P2P exchange  P2P is a unique decentralized exchange of cryptocurrencies directly between users. The main feature is the ability to make foreign exchange transactions without the participation of the third parties. The main advantage of P2P exchange is the maximum security of financial transactions. The use of this type of platform protects users from government interference.  One of the main advantages of currency exchange through P2P is minimization of commission rates. Comparing with ordinary exchangers, where all operations are carried out by employees who need to receive wages, P2P works with the help of the software, therefore the commission here is much less. Due to the use of smart algorithms, this type of exchange allows you to make secure financial transactions directly linking the buyer and the seller. P2P developers offer favorable exchange conditions, both for beginners and experienced traders with a large number of transactions.   Read more https://syntera.io/articles/133

Title: [ANN][AIRDROP][SYNTERA] Syntera sharing coin
Body: Cryptocurrencies use distributed ledgers or blockchains to record information — primarily about the balance of every address for value transfer platforms (like bitcoin and most cryptocurrencies), though the approach can be extended to any kind of information. Key to the operation of the blockchain is that the network should collectively agree on the contents of the ledger: instead of authority for keeping accounts being centralised in one entity, like a bank, it is shared amongst everyone.  This requires that the network maintains consensus around the information recorded on the blockchain. How this consensus is achieved impacts the security and economic parameters of the protocol. Here are five examples of how it’s done: https://bit.ly/2MzymKB

Body: The relevance of the Sharing economy for investments  The sharing economy or the economy of common use is a new stage in the development of modern society. Its main principle is the use, not possession of anything. Such a resource can act as a material object, for example: office, housing, car, equipment, or non-material: information, skill, etc. One of the translation variants of the sharing economy is the "economy of cooperation and participation," and this can be considered its main feature.  The reasons of this non-commercial relations type origin lie in the dynamics of modern life. This rapid urbanization and periodic economic crises worsen the well-being of people. Title: [ANN][AIRDROP][SYNTERA] Syntera sharing coin
Body: Syntera Marketplace is a virtual bi-directional marketplace where customers and vendors would mutually benefit, as the first ones will get the desired product and the latter ones will be paid for providing it to the clients. So, what services does it offer?  1. Renting out any unused things. One can rent out everything he/she wants, starting from the book and ending with a car or an apartment.  2. Collaborative purchasing of goods and services. Here you will be able to find the like-minded people, who want the same thing and with whom you can split the cost of the purchase. 3. One can co-own company shares, trading accounts, bonds, and loans, cars to name just a few.          Additionally, all terms and conditions of the services listed above are set in smart contracts, provided within the Syntera blockchain platform. As you may see, this kind of service is very convenient and beneficial at the same time. Author: SYNTERA
Title: [ANN][AIRDROP][SYNTERA] Syntera sharing coin
Body: Sharing Is Caring: How Syntera Helps Your Plans To Become True   It’s not a secret, that having usual graphics processing units is not enough anymore to mine a cryptocurrency. It requires complicated and expensive mining hardware. The price of the equipment can reach thousands of US dollars and not everyone can afford it.  Syntera has a solution! Each person now can get the required capacities. Users may unite and purchase the ASICs hardware together.  Let’s take a look at the habitual situation. A family of 3 wants to buy a car. All three members will be using the car for their needs, so why not to split its cost? Before, one of them could have gathered the money from the others and simply buy a car. But what Syntera actually does now, is that it powers all the conditions of the deal by smart contracts. In this case, the family not only split the cost of the car but also co-own it. The same can be done with the mining hardware. The ownership rights can be divided between the holders in accordance with their share of the cost.  Syntera implements principles of the sharing economy and helps users to get the resources to carry out their needs. It creates the community of the people, who can cooperate and unite to reach their goals together.
